transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: I'm calling to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: I can take a look into that for you, one moment.

Speaker 2: Okay, can I get your last name and zip code?

Speaker 1: Last name is Andrade, A-N-D-R-A-D-E.

Speaker 2: Zip code is 9-9-3-5-0.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I do see you have an order with us.

Speaker 2: You're currently a member of the A.G.V. Viagra through Pfizer.

Speaker 1: One thing I wanted to mention, sir, is if I were to cancel these orders for you,

Speaker 2: unfortunately the doctor would also delete the prescription.

Speaker 1: And you wouldn't be able to order these in the future.

Speaker 2: However, I can always switch you over to our six-month plan.

Speaker 1: That way you can always call us when you need them or call us to delay them.

Speaker 2: I tried to look for like somewhere so I could put like a Pfizer script.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can definitely do that for you.

Speaker 2: Normally it's easier to the phone because you have to adjust the script.

Speaker 1: So did you want me to make that adjustment to the six months,

Speaker 2: which is the two orders a year, but you can always call us to get them sooner

Speaker 1: or just freeze it out further?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah, you can do that.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'll set you up for that then.

Speaker 2: You're all set on that end.

Speaker 1: If you have any questions, give us a call back, but I hope you have a good day.

Speaker 2: All right, thank you.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
